DESCRIPTION. — 
15 specimens
examined. Small frogs with a triangular head and a very pointed and short snout. Morphologically sturdy with strong limbs, adapted for burrowing (
Fig. 4A
). Skin soft and smooth (
Laurent 1972
; 
Rödel 2000
). Dorsal colouration of living frogs yellowish with some dark brown spots on the back. In alcohol, yellow colour whitish dorsally and ventrally.
